data.name: textBoxAMD.Text
data.value: AMD (Age related macular degeneration) is a painless eye condition that gradually leads to loss of central vision. It stands as the 3rd most common cause of vision loss in the world. Symptoms include difficulty reading text, colors appearing less vibrant and difficulty recognizing faces. Symptoms can come in the form of eye floaters, dark shadowy specks that fly across your vision.
